Ubuntu: https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/grub2/+bug/386922
Description: Remove some verbose messages printed before reading the
 configuration file. In some ways this is awkward because it makes debugging
 harder, but it's a requirement for a smooth-looking boot process; we may be
 able to do better in future.
UbuntuSpecific: Removes status messages that are arguably useful for
 debugging; we think it looks tidier, but upstream isn't interested.

